The paper deals with the problem of releasing sensitive user data while preserving privacy, which is a core concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The focus is on count queries, which involves analyzing the frequency of certain events in a dataset, and designing mechanisms to release data associated with a group of n individuals. This involves optimization and linear programming, which are common techniques in the fields of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses data distributions and privacy parameters, which are relevant to the field of databases (cs.DB) and information theory (cs.IT).
